The two suspects accused of the murder of Zamani Kleinbooi, 35, at the Crossmoor informal settlement are due to appear at the Chatsworth Magistrate’s Court. The suspects, aged 22 and 25, were arrested on Tuesday following a swift investigation conducted by the Chatsworth SAPS Serious and Violent Crimes Unit. Captain Nqobile Gwala, KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said that the fatal stabbing of Kleinbooi occurred on 25 October at around 1pm. She said: “It is alleged that an altercation took place at an informal settlement in Crossmoor where two victims were stabbed resulting in the death of 35-year-old Zamani Kleinbooi. The victim was found with multiple stab wounds on the body and the second victim was treated at a local hospital and thereafter discharged.”
An investigation was immediately launched by the unit resulting in the apprehension of the suspects. The swift arrest of the suspects has been applauded by the provincial commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula. He said: “As we approach the season of goodwill, police are cautioning residents to live in harmony. Police will arrest offenders who do not conform to the law of the country.